Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 101
Edition:
Quote: <i> shit a brick </i>exclamation of annoyance and/or surprise; eg Maurice Shadbolt's <i>Among the Cinders,</i> 1965: ` `A queer thing. Something psychological.' `Shit a brick,' he said.' c. 1925. NZA.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1989
Source: Dinkum Kiwi Dictionary, The
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 93
Edition:
Quote: <i>shit a brick and build a house</i> exclamation of surprise, perhaps at some unexpected luck; eg `All season he's sat out on the wing like a spectator and in the last game he runs in four flippin' tries. Shit a brick and build a house, that Roche is tinny.'
Notes:
